== Association Football? ==

The black and ambers website states that Richard Garnons Williams also played international football for Wales. Using the www.wfda.co.uk site, I have scanned through all international Welsh games from the 1870s and 1880s and have not found RDG Williams among the players. There may be confusion with Richard Parry Williams, who played for Carnarvon Athletic and faced Scotland in 1886. [[User:FruitMonkey|FruitMonkey]] ([[User talk:FruitMonkey|talk]]) 07:17, 16 April 2009 (UTC)
:[[E. H. D. Sewell]] says that when RDGW was asked to 'fill a gap in the Welsh XI, that he should play as goalkeeper, which he did.'
